(secondQuint)International Multicenter, Observational, Non-Interventional Prospective Study of Azilsartan Medoxomil in Participants With Arterial Hypertension Who Are Overweight or Obese in the Russian Federation and The Republic of Kazakhstan.

 The drug being tested in this study is called azilsartan medoxomil.

 Azilsartan medoxomil is being tested to treat people who have hypertension.

 This study will look at the clinic systolic and diastolic blood pressure (SBP, DBP) in obese participants who will be prescribed with azilsartan medoxomil by physician.

 The study will enroll approximately 1916 patients.

 All participants will be asked to take azilsartan medoxomil as prescribed by their physician according to local SmPC.

 This multi-center trial will be conducted in the Russian Federation and the Republic of Kazakhstan.

 The overall duration of study for observation will be approximately 6 months.

 Participants will make multiple visits to the clinic as assigned by each physician according to their routine practice, in every 3 months.

